That's the way many in the disability sector have interpreted this bill.

1494
01:31:29.398 --> 01:31:33.298
It may not be the intent of it, but for us, always fighting

1495
01:31:33.338 --> 01:31:36.838
for inclusion, that's the message it sends to us.

1496
01:31:36.898 --> 01:31:39.958
We as a family have missed out on many opportunities.

1497
01:31:40.458 --> 01:31:44.398
We've chosen to be actively involved in our son's life and still

1498
01:31:44.478 --> 01:31:48.098
are. Even though he flats with his mates, I spend at

1499
01:31:48.198 --> 01:31:51.068
least half a day a week supporting him, and often more.

1500
01:31:52.018 --> 01:31:54.578
But there is a cost, and it's not just a financial one.

1501
01:31:55.858 --> 01:31:59.488
Point three, we've always viewed our relationship with the

1502
01:31:59.638 --> 01:32:00.958
state as a partnership.

1503
01:32:02.098 --> 01:32:04.538
We do our bit, the state does its bit.

1504
01:32:04.898 --> 01:32:08.018
And like all other citizens, we have that relationship.

1505
01:32:08.598 --> 01:32:12.418
But apart from the fact that our support for Travis has never gone away for

1506
01:32:12.458 --> 01:32:13.758
46 years,

1507
01:32:14.898 --> 01:32:18.498
usually your support for your children

1508
01:32:18.578 --> 01:32:22.238
dwindles when a person reaches the age of 18 or their

1509
01:32:22.278 --> 01:32:26.098
20s. The untie whanau support for Travis is for life.

1510
01:32:26.878 --> 01:32:30.658
We expect the state to be there in partnership for its most

1511
01:32:30.698 --> 01:32:34.418
vulnerable citizens. This bill does not send that message to me.

1512
01:32:35.338 --> 01:32:39.218
The definition of family, what we refer to as natural supports in the disability

1513
01:32:39.338 --> 01:32:42.878
sector, in the 46 years I've been involved with many disability

1514
01:32:42.958 --> 01:32:46.718
organizations and parent groups, I have never met a parent who's not

1515
01:32:46.758 --> 01:32:49.018
wanted the best for their disabled family member.

1516
01:32:49.998 --> 01:32:53.938
Their contributions are huge and should be acknowledged and valued.

1517
01:32:54.758 --> 01:32:58.448
To have the family listed out in the way it is in the bill seems

1518
01:32:58.518 --> 01:33:02.148
rather contemptuous of the years of support willingly given to this

1519
01:33:02.178 --> 01:33:03.378
country by families.

1520
01:33:04.038 --> 01:33:04.238
Mm.

1521
01:33:04.478 --> 01:33:08.258
So I ask you, why include that list and at the same time exclude

1522
01:33:08.278 --> 01:33:09.728
disabled people's voices?

1523
01:33:10.738 --> 01:33:13.838
The bill stigmatizes us as a family even more than we are

1524
01:33:13.878 --> 01:33:17.858
now. Always seeking that extra support from a huge list of

1525
01:33:18.198 --> 01:33:22.038
people. It's like going around with a begging bowl. Back to the charity discourse.

1526
01:33:22.948 --> 01:33:26.878
Point five, the very disturbing secondary legislation, the extraordinary powers

1527
01:33:26.918 --> 01:33:30.658
given to the minister, which might not be invoked by this minister, but it leaves

1528
01:33:30.697 --> 01:33:32.258
it wide open in the future.

1529
01:33:33.078 --> 01:33:36.698
Of particular concern, and no doubt it's been mentioned by many others, is

1530
01:33:36.738 --> 01:33:40.298
income and asset testing along with decisions around a person's disability.

1531
01:33:40.908 --> 01:33:44.178
That's very worrying, especially when linked to the definition of family.

1532
01:33:45.198 --> 01:33:48.978
Are you really going to ask my children or professionals to give up part of their

1533
01:33:48.998 --> 01:33:51.248
professional lives to be their brother's caregivers?

1534
01:33:52.218 --> 01:33:55.538
DSS has historically always been needs-based.

1535
01:33:56.088 --> 01:33:59.338
This apparent change has never been signaled in any meetings or

1536
01:33:59.378 --> 01:34:00.827
communications from the government.

1537
01:34:01.518 --> 01:34:05.178
Some laws do have asset and means testing, but not disability support

1538
01:34:05.278 --> 01:34:08.678
services. So why introduce it in this bill right now?

1539
01:34:09.518 --> 01:34:12.158
It's very tough out there in the disability sector.

1540
01:34:12.578 --> 01:34:16.038
We are all survivors of, at times, a very indifferent

1541
01:34:16.118 --> 01:34:19.438
system. This bill has created a huge amount of

1542
01:34:19.478 --> 01:34:23.238
anxiety. What I do know is, in the 46 years I've been

1543
01:34:23.318 --> 01:34:26.528
supporting Travis, we've had 17 education ministers,

1544
01:34:26.978 --> 01:34:30.698
13 MSD ministers, 14 disability issues

1545
01:34:30.818 --> 01:34:32.898
ministers, and 20 ministers of health.

1546
01:34:33.538 --> 01:34:37.258
And what I also know is that when you've all retired and look back at your

1547
01:34:37.298 --> 01:34:40.338
legacy in Parliament, think about these two things.

1548
01:34:40.978 --> 01:34:44.338
Will this bill be a moment of pride for you?

1549
01:34:44.398 --> 01:34:48.258
And also know that in the disability sector, we know that politicians

1550
01:34:48.298 --> 01:34:51.878
come and go, but families are there forever. 46 years.

1551
01:34:52.808 --> 01:34:52.808
Mm.

1552
01:34:52.838 --> 01:34:56.458
This bill signals a lifetime of having conditional relationships, asking

1553
01:34:56.538 --> 01:35:00.338
extended families, "Can you, would you support us in any way?"

1554
01:35:00.818 --> 01:35:03.718
And not knowing how the state would carry on supporting you, if at all.

1555
01:35:04.238 --> 01:35:06.878
So I ask you in all conscience, where is the hope?

1556
01:35:07.518 --> 01:35:07.648
Mm.

1557
01:35:07.838 --> 01:35:08.698
Where is the value?

1558
01:35:09.538 --> 01:35:13.518
And if you vote for this bill in its current form, is it really, is this the

1559
01:35:13.578 --> 01:35:14.378
best you can do?

1560
01:35:15.438 --> 01:35:15.698
Mm.

1561
01:35:15.918 --> 01:35:18.058
Thank you, Colleen. We are over time, and I'll just say questions to crack it.

1562
01:35:18.958 --> 01:35:21.518
Thank you, Mr. Chair. Quick question. Thanks, Colleen.

1563
01:35:22.678 --> 01:35:26.368
Your third point, to remove all reference to secondary

1564
01:35:26.618 --> 01:35:30.478
legislation. Now, the minister's rationale for this is that she's creating the

1565
01:35:30.498 --> 01:35:32.758
framework and then the detail will come later.

1566
01:35:33.218 --> 01:35:35.998
